## Bug Report

Please answer these questions before submitting your issue. Thanks!

### 1. Minimal reproduce step (Required)

The following test case triggered an unexpected error `baseBuiltinFunc.vecEvalInt() should never be called, please contact the TiDB team for help`

```
CREATE TABLE t0(c0 BOOL);
INSERT IGNORE  INTO t0 VALUES (false);
SET @b = NULL;
SET @c = NULL;
PREPARE prepare_query FROM 'SELECT ((NULLIF(?, ?))OR(t0.c0)) FROM t0';
EXECUTE prepare_query USING @b,@c;
```

### 2. What did you expect to see? (Required)

No error.

### 3. What did you see instead (Required)

`baseBuiltinFunc.vecEvalInt() should never be called, please contact the TiDB team for help`

### 4. What is your TiDB version? (Required)

